# MegaAppX Enterprise Resource Management

## Overview
MegaAppX is a comprehensive Linux-based application designed for enterprise resource management. This project is part of the RHCSA practical training and provides robust solutions for configuration management, logging, and user data handling.

## Key Features
- Advanced user management and authentication
- Real-time resource monitoring
- Automated backup and recovery
- Comprehensive logging system
- Multi-tier caching architecture
- Scalable database integration

## System Requirements
- Linux kernel 5.x or higher
- MySQL/MariaDB 8.0+
- Redis 6.0+
- Python 3.8+
- 4GB RAM minimum
- 20GB disk space

## Installation Guide
1. System Preparation
   ```bash
   sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
   sudo apt install python3-pip redis-server mysql-server
   ```

2. Application Setup
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/enterprise/megaappx.git
   cd megaappx
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

3. Configuration
   ```bash
   cp config.example.cfg config.cfg
   ./setup.sh --init
   ```

